commitResults.messageTitle: Add Patient.java class to represent a patient in the address book
commitResults.messageBody:
- Defines fields for patient details such as name, phone, email, address, doctor in charge, and guardian.
- Implements validation for required fields.
- Ensures immutability and proper equality/hashCode implementations.
- Provides toString method for string representation.
- Supports comparison based on patient identity (same name) and full equality.

commitResults.messageTitle: Refactor CSS Structure: Separate Color and Layout Styles
commitResults.messageBody:
- Moved all color-related styles to DarkTheme.css to centralize color configuration.
- Moved all UI layout and sizing-related styles (e.g., padding, font sizes, borders) to Extensions.css for better separation of concerns.
- Added LightTheme.css to provide an alternative color scheme for light-themed UI.
- Ensured all UI elements follow the new structure for color and layout styling.

commitResults.messageTitle: Add Dark/Light Theme Toggle with Persistent Storage
commitResults.messageBody:
- Implemented UI toggle for switching between dark and light themes.
- Stored user preference to retain selected theme on subsequent app launches.

commitResults.messageBody: - Fixed errors and updated test cases to ensure proper functionality.

commitResults.messageTitle: Synchronize theme between MainWindow and HelpWindow
commitResults.messageBody:
- Added a constructor in HelpWindow to accept and apply the initial theme state.
- Modified MainWindow to pass the current theme state when creating the HelpWindow.
- Ensured HelpWindow follows the theme on startup and updates whenever the theme is toggled in MainWindow.

commitResults.messageTitle: Refactor stylesheets management and enhance logging
commitResults.messageBody:
- Extracted stylesheet update logic into a dedicated updateStyleSheets() method.
- Updated theme initialization and toggling to use the new method.
- Added detailed logging for theme changes.
